description.narrative: The Humanitarian Action Plan for Children in addition to the Health component of the HRP was implemented: 80,920 of the 82,068 children living on IDP sites and enclaves had access to care in 13 health districts; 2 rounds of response Polio epidemic in the Lake Chad Basin and 4 rounds of response to epidemic of cVDPV2, were organized in children 0-5 years in 21 of 35 health with 1,001,508 children under 5 have been vaccinated against polio; and 256,553 children 6-59 months vaccinated during the response to the measles epidemic in 7 districts. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
